FBIS4-40201 "drsov115_d_94007" FBIS-SOV-94-115 Daily Report 15 Jun 1994 Regional Affairs Russia, Bashkorstan Treaty To Be Drafted Russia, Bashkorstan Treaty To Be Drafted LD1506103294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1007 GMT 15 Jun 94 LD1506103294 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [Text] Moscow June 15 ITAR-TASS -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin today set up a commission to prepare a bilateral treaty between the Russian Federation and one of its constituent parts, the Republic of Bashkortostan. The treaty is due to divide powers between the federation and its component republic and decide on the delegation of powers between the bodies of state authorities of Russia and Bashkortostan, the presidential press service announced today. Vice-Premier Sergey Shakhray is appointed to head the commission. Earlier, Moscow signed a treaty with Tatarstan, another component republic of the Russian Federation.
